During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders announced that President Trump will be donating his second quarter salary of $100,000 to the Department of Education. Secretary of Education Betsy DeVos joined Sanders to explain that the funds will be used to host a STEM-focused camp for students. Sanders also discussed the President's disappointment with Attorney General Jeff Sessions, but stated that he still wants Sessions to continue leading the Department of Justice. The briefing also touched on topics such as the President's decision to ban transgender individuals from serving in the military, tax reform, and healthcare.